    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-06-01T07:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-06-01T07:10:00-05:00" n="157"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                <head>157. Minutes of the Secretary of State’s Staff Meeting, Washington, June 1,
                    1976, 8:10 a.m.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d157fn1">Source: National
                        Archives, <gloss target="#t_rg">RG</gloss> 59, Transcripts of Secretary of
                        State <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName>’s Staff
                        Meetings, 1973–1977, E5177, Box 10. Secret.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d157fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName> and his aides
                        discussed military aid to Indonesia.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1976-06-01T08:10:00-04:00">June 1, 1976, 8:10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>In Attendance - Tuesday, June 1, 1976</head>
                    <item>Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a"
                            >Kissinger</persName> - Chairman</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_t">T</gloss> Mr. <persName corresp="#p_maw-carlyle-e"
                            >Maw</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_m">M</gloss> Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_eagleburger-lawrence-s">Eagleburger</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>C Mr. <persName corresp="#p_sonnenfeldt-helmut-c">Sonnenfeldt</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_af">AF</gloss> Mr. Schaufele</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_ea">EA</gloss> Mr. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c"
                            >Habib</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_eur">EUR</gloss> Mr. Hartman</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_nea">NEA</gloss> Mr. Atherton</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_inr">INR</gloss> Mr. Saunders</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_s-p">S/P</gloss> Mr. <persName corresp="#p_lord-winston"
                            >Lord</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_eb">EB</gloss> Mr. Greenwald</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_s-prs">S/PRS</gloss> Mr. Funseth</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_pm">PM</gloss> Mr. Stern (Acting)</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_io">IO</gloss> Mr. <persName corresp="#p_lewis-samuel-w"
                            >Lewis</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_l">L</gloss> Mr. Leigh</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_s-s">S/S</gloss> Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_springsteen-george-s">Springsteen</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_s">S</gloss> Mr. Aherne</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_s">S</gloss> Mr. <persName corresp="#p_covey-james-p"
                            >Covey</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="d157-2" n="2" xml:id="d157-2"/>
                <p>[Omitted is material unrelated to Indonesia.]</p>
                <p>MR. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c">HABIB</persName>: The only other thing
                    I want to make sure you’re aware of is the first act in the integration of Timor
                    in Indonesia has taken place. There’s a declaration by the Indonesian Assembly
                    to integrate. Our guess is that the National Day will be the formal day of
                    integration. I doubt that there will be any further difficulty. It will go very
                    smoothly.</p>
                <p>SECRETARY <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">KISSINGER</persName>: Have we
                    reopened our military-supply position?</p>
                <p>MR. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c">HABIB</persName>: The supply position
                    has never been shut down.</p>
                <p>SECRETARY <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">KISSINGER</persName>: Come on
                    — you know what I’m asking you.</p>
                <p>MR. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c">HABIB</persName>: New commitments will
                    be made very shortly by our distinguished colleague (referring to Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_maw-carlyle-e">Maw</persName>). New commitments are not being
                    made.</p>
                <p>SECRETARY <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">KISSINGER</persName>:
                    Today?</p>
                <p>MR. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c">HABIB</persName>: No. We’ve got one
                    contract we’re holding off on. We have some helicopters with Sikorsky — which
                    should be signed this week.</p>
                <p>SECRETARY <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">KISSINGER</persName>: Plus
                    we’re not letting them</p>
                <pb facs="d157-3" n="3" xml:id="d157-3"/>
                <p>MR. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c">HABIB</persName>: You end up with a
                    case like Chile, where we cut it off.</p>
                <p>SECRETARY <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">KISSINGER</persName>: With the
                    result that they cut off all the rest. There was never any question of having it
                    cut off from Chile. There is more or less the same thing — we’re cutting them
                    off — and, eventually, the Congress will cut them off. You’ll never get a letter
                    from Humphrey that you can use.</p>
                <p>MR. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c">HABIB</persName>: I’ll send it to
                    you.</p>
                <p>[Omitted is material unrelated to Indonesia.]</p>
            </div>
